Nested class :  A nested class is a class that is defined inside another class.
üîπ Why Nested Classes Are Used?
    - To group logically related classes
    - To increase encapsulation
    - To access private members of outer class
    - To make code more readable and maintainable

Note:- Outer class static q nhi hoti ?
- Top-level (outer) class static ho hi nahi sakti because:
   - static ka matlab hota hai kisi enclosing class se belong karna, Lekin outer class ke paas koi enclosing class hoti hi nahi/Outer class khud kisi class ke andar nahi hoti.
   - so it can be access access directly if in same package then like this : A a = new A();  or if Different package then like this : packageA.A a = new packageA.A();

Types of Nested Classes in Java :
1Ô∏è‚É£ Static Nested Class : 
- Does not need outer class object
- Static Nested Class can DIRECTLY access only static members of outer class. but creating object of outer class also non-static can be access.
- is static nested class ke ander sab kuch ho skta hai like,non-static variables , methods , constructors, static methods , variables. similar to any other class.
- static nested class bnane ka fayda :
                    - object creation me or outer class static memeber access me,   A.B  obj = new A.B();
                    - static nested class me only static methods are avialable then object v bnane ki need nhi hai directly can be access like A.B.display();
- static nested class par saare 4 access modifiers lag sakte hain:  visibility outer + nested dono decide karte hain

2Ô∏è‚É£ Non-Static Nested Class (Inner Class) :
Types:
    - Member Inner Class/ regular inner class :- Non-static class jo outer class ke andar hoti hai,aur outer class ke object se tightly bound hoti hai but kisi v function ke body se baher hogi.
       
         - inner class se outer class kaise call kr skte ho / data access kr skte ho ? outer-clas-name.this.outerClassMemeber/methodName.
         - inner classes aaps me v inheritance kr skti hai. 
         - how to create inner class obje ? OuterClass obj = new OuterClass(); // outer    Outer.Inner inObj = obj.new Inner(); // inner class obj

    - Local Inner Class :- aisi koi v class jo outer class ke ander ho as well as outer class kisi method, constructor ya block ke andar declare hoti hai,
        - this class can't be static, private, protected..etc not allowed
        - benifit : Method ke variables access karne ke liye, Agar koi class sirf ek hi method me use honi hai bahar kahin kaam nahi aayegi to usko method ke andar rakhte hain.

    - Anonymous Inner Class : aisi class jiska koi v name nhi ho, ye use me ata hai incomplete method ko implement krne k liye jaise abstract class ke methods, interfaces ke method.
 way to define :
        NoNameClass nn = new NoNameClass() {
            @Override
            void display() {
                
            }
        };
        nn.display();


------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Java Generics :
Syntax=:-  className<T> where T means type
Use case:- suppose there is a class which has display method which is displaying value as per requirement sometimes, integer type, double or string etc so we use convention T which is replace
           with actual value at runtime.
Note:- there is concept of bounded generic class eg - ClassName<T extends CollegeClassName> isme college class name se jo v class extend kr rhi hogi whi accept hoga kewl
      kuch common convention like :   T -> type ke liye
                                      E  -> Element
                                      K  -> key
                                      V  -> value
